 <H1>Summary of Schema Refinement</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>If a relation is in BCNF, it is free of redundancies that can be detected using FDs.  Thus, trying to ensure that all relations are in BCNF is a good heuristic.
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>If a relation is not in BCNF, we can try to decompose it into a collection of BCNF relations.
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Must consider whether all FDs are preserved.  If a lossless-join, dependency preserving decomposition into BCNF is not possible (or unsuitable, given typical queries), should consider decomposition into 3NF.
<LI>Decompositions should be carried out and/or re-examined while keeping performance requirements in mind.</UL></UL></P>
